Attributes.description: Analysis of water resources from a water-in-ecosystem perspective. Application to natural, managed, and urban systems, considering ecological interactions with hydrological processes. Exploration of biogeochemical processes related to water quality, and human impacts on water resources.
Attributes.prereq: Pre-reqs: One of GEOB 305, GEOS 305, EOSC 325, EOSC 329.
